=Description=

"LexDAO engages in various activities, including research and development in legal engineering, training initiatives, and advocacy for open-source law and blockchain-based dispute resolution. They also collaborate with educational institutions and nonprofits, focusing on student-led projects and the advancement of public goods, and provide consultancy services in web3 development and decentralized organizational structures." [https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Spepip82i31lZ3wwEF8-ppAbhJH3s5kd3OfYLC7UTnI/edit?usp=sharing])

"LexDAO decided to create a **roster of certified Legal Engineers** as a first step to create quality standards for the emerging space. Individuals who want to get this certification have to go through a long process, culminating in a vote granting the certification from peers."


=Status=

"LexDAO [Corpus](https://github.com/lexDAO/LexCorpus)

A collection of tools, code and legal resources designed to support the LexDAO community and the broader legal engineering ecosystem. It includes templates for smart contracts, legal research papers, and educational materials. 

LexDAO is actively developing smart contract projects designed to offer **arbitration services** for individuals and organizations; these projects can be utilized directly as services provided by LexDAO to resolve conflicts between parties but, given the nature of the **open source code**, anyone can adopt and integrate it into their own solutions or even offer the service independently."

(https://commonseconomy.notion.site/What-Are-Legal-Engineers-building-9dbfd39062844c7eb8b0396c591608c1)

